Q1. Write a python program to accepts value of radius from user and calculate the area of a circle using
function. (Use 3.14 as the value of π).


def area_circle(radius):
    return 3.14 * radius * radius
r = float(input("Enter radius: "))
area = area_circle(r)
print("Area of circle:", area)



Q2. Write a python program to create a list, string and tuple in python. Apply random module to display
unique multiple random elements from above created sequence type.


import random
my_list = [10, 20, 30, 40, 50]
my_tuple = (1, 2, 3, 4, 5)
my_string = "PYTHON"
list_random = random.sample(my_list, 3)
tuple_random = random.sample(my_tuple, 3)
string_random = random.sample(my_string, 3)
print("Random elements from list:", list_random)
print("Random elements from tuple:", tuple_random)
print("Random elements from string:", string_random)








